comment.author: 41909278@N08
comment._content:
This is a very interesting photograph. It shows an AT-6 in RAF markings, with the identifier NA66 on the rear fuselage. This not an NA-66, but more likely an NA-88, identical in most ways to the USAAF's AT-6C and AT-6D. These aircraft served in Commonwealth countries as Harvards Mk IIA and III.

Doug MacPhail
